social_posts.post_text: * SOUND ON* I owe @ropunawa a huge thank you for this fantastic tie. I added in a half rope, just for a little extra fun and *security* 😂😂😂 I love you so much @calliope.atx 😘 (this video is pushing the edge, but was just too cute to not try to share 🤞🤞🤞)

This woman exemplifies the meaning of strength to me. I can’t wait to continue to explore with you, as you embark on this next journey in your life @calliope.atx Your trust means the world to me, and I am grateful everyday, for you in my life. You are going to be an INCREDIBLE mama and we are going to continue to learn more and grow more together through this. Love you so so much 💜💜💜
I wanted to give @calliope.atx a chance to explore a bit in her body and really sink in to this futo. It has nothing to do with how adorable she is as she whimpers and wiggles 🤓😍

I’m going to go as often as I possibly can now and knock this bad girl out 💜 (money is hard! If you wanna help, DM me for my deets and I promise to send dirty rewards, if that’s your thing!! I love labbing with my loves. Spent the night with @calliope.atx and @shaktibliss.tantricwitch last night, playing with ties and ideas for our performance coming up at TKF. I think it’s going to be pretty damn special ❤️❤️❤️

Gosh, I am lucky. 🥹🥹🥹 So looking forward to this performance with @calliope.atx and @shaktibliss.tantricwitch at @texaskfest ❤️ swipe for a bonus pic of my lovely lady and I at Eeyore’s Birthday this weekend ☺️

LONG STORY TIME: 

This weekend, I had a really incredible moment. I was in the woods, with a bunch of my favorite hippies. I brought my cube out, and got to use it for an art piece for the first time. I spent hours on an abstract structure using 1000 feet of cord to create an enterable space to hang out in. You enter through a vulva shaped door and we had two chairs in there to chill in. I watched a lot of people have moments in there, but there was one, that was absolutely the most special of them all for me. 

6 months ago, I asked a girl out, who I have known for years, but never truly known. I always admired her at parties and loved the small times we shared together, but I could have never predicted, how instantaneously and deeply I would fall for her. 

6 months ago, she had never been in rope before. She trusted me to begin exploring this space with her. Since then we have flown to Alaska to teach together, performed together, and began this journey of learning what rope could be for us in a collection of crazy exciting moments.

This weekend, in my cube, in my art, she trusted me to do her very first full suspension. Everyone wants to rush in rope, but taking 6 months to develop the trust, connection and knowledge about her body, made this moment beyond special. We went into it with no expectations and a complete willingness to not *succeed*. She killed it. Not only did she get up in the air, we were able to transition, and she did a full inversion. 

Despite having many physical limitations from injuries in her past, we were able to learn over time what would work for her, and create an incredibly special experience, in as safe of a way as possible in this dangerous game we play. 

Special doesn’t describe it. 

I’m not going to tag her, for family visibility reasons, but she knows who she is, and hopefully knows how much love and gratitude I have for her and her trust. 

If you made it this far reading my novel, I’m impressed. It just felt important to document it for my own memories 💜💜💜

Swipe to see how far we got in the first session, but I wanted to show the happiness on my face first 😊

I am damn excited to have started this piece. I’ve been dreaming about the artist’s work for years and am thrilled to have finally taken the steps to start this process for myself. Thanks to the people who have supported me and who made (well rewarded) donations to help me make this happen. This project is going to take a while, so remember that if you ever want to help out, I generously thank with pics and vids! 😅😘
